article_title: Wisconsin illustrates weirdness of U.S. Senate

article_metadata.description: The New York Times website has a short video up this morning featuring the two senators from Wisconsin, Ron Johnson and Tammy Baldwin.Both are freshmen. Republican Johnson is a righty businessman with political roots in the Tea Party who says in the video that his uppermost goal as a U.S. senator is to be "the vote" to repeal Obamacare.

og.description: Wisconsin senators cancel each other out on 76 percent of votes.
